annotationA: Troponin I; Troponin I is the ATPase inhibitory subunit of troponin in the thin filament regulatory complex. Involved in the development and maintenance of muscle and nervous system. May also be involved in the cytoskeletal apparatus
annotationB: Myofilin, isoform B; It is involved in the biological process described with: wing disc development; chaeta development; skeletal muscle myosin thick filament assembly
